			<description><![CDATA[Avni.  Perhaps reading the response to Dinesh's message might help.  Also you may want to take some quite time to look back on what happened 5 years ago that made your attitude change so much.  Dissatisfaction with life usually comes from dissatisfaction with the self.  It is good that you have realized that your unhappiness and anger is coming from you, because this means that you also have the power to change.  Understanding that originally you are a peaceful being filled with qualities of love, peace, happiness and truth allows you to access these qualities.  They are yours - you don't have to get them from anywhere else.  Meditation is a good way to access and experience these qualities within yourself.  By spending time in introversion, and experiencing your qualities you will then be able to bring these into your life as you in turn become extrovert. (come into action).]]></description>
