			<description><![CDATA[Dinesh:  It is good that you are taking such benefit from Happiness Unlimited.  Regarding your son.  There is really nothing you can do to diminish your son's temper - he has to do it for himself.  The first step would be for him to recognize that he has a problem and then want to fix it. Then he could investigate for himself different avenues that he could take.  There are organizations that do 'Anger Management courses.  The Brahma Kumaris also offer this at some of their centers which include meditation - which is very helpful as there is also the opportunity to connect with who we really are so that we can develop self-respect, have a deeper understanding of how to create good relationships and good actions and to receive support from God.  Regarding how you deal with your sons temper - there are always choices of how to respond and with the development of your own spiritual journey you will begin to make choices that will help you and indirectly your son.  Having pure and powerful good wishes and love with understanding will definitely help everyone.]]></description>
